8','default','Users can select the <em>printer-friendly version</em> link visible at the bottom of a book page to generate a printer-friendly display of the page and all of its subsections. ','none');
INSERT INTO `locales_source` VALUES ('1205',' modules/book/book.module:1009','default','Users with the <em>administer book outlines</em> permission can add a post of any content type to a book, by selecting the appropriate book while editing the post or by using the interface available on the post\'s <em>outline</em> tab.','none'),('1206',' modules/book/book.module:1011','default','For more information, see the online handbook entry for <a href=\"@book\">Book module</a>.','none'),('1207',' modules/book/book.module:1014','default','The book module offers a means to organize a collection of related posts, collectively known as a book. When viewed, these posts automatically display links to adjacent book pages, providing a simple navigation system for creating and reviewing structured content.','none'),('1208',' modules/book/book.module:1016','default','The outline feature allows you to include posts in the <a href=\"@book\">book hierarchy</a>, as well as move them within the hierarchy or to <a href=\"@book-admin\">reorder an entire book</a>.','none'),('1209',' modules/book/book.module:43','default','create new books','none'),('1210',' modules/book/book.module:43','default','access printer-friendly version','none'),('1211',' modules/book/book.module:79;108','default','Books','none'),('1212',' modules/book/book.module:80','default','Manage your site\'s book outlines.','none'),('1213',' modules/book/book.module:99','default','Re-order book pages and change titles','none'),('1214',' modules/book/book.module:122','default','Outline','none'),('1215',' modules/book/book.module:132','default','Remove from outline','none'),('1216',' modules/book/book.module:0','default','book','none'),('1217',' modules/book/book.install:29','default','Book page','none'),('1218',' modules/book/book.install:31','default','A <em>book page</em> is a page of content, organized into a collection of related entries collectively known as a <em>book</em>. A <em>book page</em> automatically displays lin